Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Halve and peel the @red onion{1}, then cut each half into 3 wedges.

Pop the potato chunks and onion wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @Central American style spice mix{1%tsp}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell peppers{2} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Chop the @tomatoes{2%medium} into 2cm chunks. Drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}.

Put the pepper, tomatoes and sweetcorn onto another #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with salt and pepper, then stir through the @chipotle paste{20%g} to coat everything.

Once the potatoes have roasted for ~{10%minutes}, pop the pepper tray onto the middle shelf to cook until the veg has softened, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Once everything's cooked, add the pepper, tomato and sweetcorn to the tray with the potatoes and onion. Toss to combine.

Share the chipotle hash between your #bowls{} and crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g}.

Serve with a dollop of @soured cream{75%g} on top.

Enjoy!